<div id="review_34094741" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/34094741" />
    <a title="Gwenda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1155356-gwenda"><img alt="Gwenda" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/34094741?book_show_action=true">Sep 28, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gwenda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gwenda" href="/user/show/1155356-gwenda">Gwenda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer34094741" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4823620404712967217">I haven&apos;t found much LDS fiction that I enjoyed, but this book was an absolute delight. As historical fiction, it used a lot of real people and settings. Guess what? I found several references to my great-great-grandfather Redick Newton Allred in this book! His nickname was &quot;the bulldog&quot; because he was tenacious about doing what the prophet asked him to do. He headed up the supply wagons that went out to rescue the two handcart companies in desperate situations. Since his provision wagons were l</span>
  <span id="freeText4823620404712967217" style="display:none">I haven't found much LDS fiction that I enjoyed, but this book was an absolute delight. As historical fiction, it used a lot of real people and settings. Guess what? I found several references to my great-great-grandfather Redick Newton Allred in this book! His nickname was "the bulldog" because he was tenacious about doing what the prophet asked him to do. He headed up the supply wagons that went out to rescue the two handcart companies in desperate situations. Since his provision wagons were loaded down with supplies, they took longer to travel. At a certain point in western Wyoming, he "hunkered down" with the provisions and waited until the handcart pioneers were found; then he brought the wagons forward to meet them. It was a long wait and most of his men gave up and went back to Salt Lake City, but he wouldn't give up. His story has also been told by President Eyring at least twice in conference. Makes me proud!!! Aside from that personal connection, this story really shows you how the pioneers who suffered in these companies felt. I can't relate to the incredible amount of physical suffering and scarcity they experienced. Not a bad book to read during Thanksgiving week!</span>
  <a data-text-id="4823620404712967217" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


